result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

ADDRESS INFO for Elwyn N. Fossedal
Current: 1421 Boulder Ave., Helena, MT 59601 United States  (Effective: 03-10-2014)
Prior: 1620 Wedgewood Drive, Richland Center, WI 53581

Three cases called together ( 13CF82, 13CF83 & 14CF9). Attorney Gerald C Opgenorth in court with Defendant Elwyn N. Fossedal. Prosecuting Atty Jennifer A. Harper appeared for State of Wisconsin. DA Harper states plea agreement which is as follows: 13CF83 def to plead G or NC to count 1, counts 2 and 3 are dismissed but read in and in 13CF82 & 14CF9 charges are dismissed and read in. Atty O presents plea questionnaire/waiver of rights. Court's colloquy re. prelim waiver. Court accepts def's waiver to prelim in 13CF83, binds def over for trial. Atty O waives formal reading of information in 13CF83. Court informs def of the charge/max possible penalties. Def enters NC plea to information filed. Court's colloquy re. plea questionnaire/waiver of rights. Court finds factual basis for charges. Further colloquy. Court accepts plea of NC and finds def is entering plea freely, voluntarily and intelligently. Court finds def guilty, directs clerk to withhold entering JOC for a diversion agreement on Ct 1 (24 months). Ct 2 & 3 are dismissed and read in. 13CF82 & 14CF9 are dismissed and read in. Comment by DA and Atty O. Court will adopt the diversion agreement as written. Bond stands as written.
Status conference on March 19, 2014 at 01:30 pm.

DA Harper, Def, and Atty. Opgenorth for status in 13CF82, 13CF83 and 14CF9.  DA states that the parties are waiting for federal case to resolve; ask for further status in these matters.  Status conference scheduled for 03-19-2014 at 01:30 pm.
Status conference on February 19, 2014 at 09:00 am.
Defendant is to comply with all conditions of the amended release order in the case of United States of America vs Elwin Nels Fossedal 13-cr-159-wmc.

Matters 14CF19, 13CF83, and 13CF82 are held together. 14CF19 is an inital appearance. 13CF83 and 13CF82 are being held for bond modification.

DA Harper appears for the State, EF appears with Atty nG Opgnenorth. Matter 14CF19--Atty O waives formal reading of complaint, court reads max penalties. Atty O does not waive prelim hearing, but does waive time period for prelim hearing. Court accepts time waiver. Matter is set for STC on 02/19/2014 at 9:00 am. $7500 signature bond. Defendant is to comply with all conditions of the amended release order in the case of United States of America vs Elwin Nels Fossedal 13 CR 159 wmc.

Matters 13CF82 & 13CF83--DA Harper asks for bond to be modified in each case to a $7500 signature bond and for defandant to comply with all conditions of the amended release order in the case of United States of America vs Elwin Nels Fossedal 13 CR 159 wmc. Court so orders.
